This paper discusses the use of data collection and mapping techniques to analyze patent information, which falls under the category of computational science (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the spatial concentration of patenting in Central and Eastern Europe, which could fall under the sub-category of digital libraries (cs.DL) or social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the dominance of foreign control over USPTO patents, which could fall under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) or software engineering (cs.SD).
